Airflow - Is an Opensource framework which can be used as an ORCHESTRATOR.
One simple example for the orchestration
========================================
SQL Databases/Web Application -> Python(extraction) -> AWS S3 ->Spark(Process and Load) -> Redshift(Warehousing)

What Airflow is not? - Airflow is not a data processing Framework.
                       Airflow is not a Real_TIME processing framework like IOT core.
                       Airflow is not an ETL tool/Framework.

Why Airflow Can't Do Real-Time Processing
1. Batch-oriented by design: Airflow is a workflow orchestrator that schedules and monitors DAGs (Directed Acyclic Graphs) on a time-based or trigger-based schedule. It processes data in discrete batches, not continuous streams.
2. Scheduler latency: The Airflow scheduler polls for new tasks at intervals (default ~5 seconds). This inherent polling delay makes sub-second or true real-time processing impossible.
3. No built-in streaming engine: Airflow has no mechanism to consume events from a message queue/stream (like Kafka topics) continuously. It lacks concepts like windowing, watermarks, or event-time processing.
4. Minimum practical interval: You can schedule DAGs as frequently as every ~1 minute, but this is micro-batching, not real-time, and puts heavy load on the scheduler/database.

