Core Components Of Airflow
===========================
- Matadata Database : like Details about your DAG's, its definitions, its scheduled time, status, task instance ...
- DAG File Processor : DAG file processor will got o your dags folder and will parse it and store the serialized DAG into the DB.
Note - serialized DAG, is something, when you write your code in Python, it converts the code for the respective DAG into a JSON representation and store that in the Database.
- API Server : The backbone where you interact, the frontend - your web server where all the components will communicate. Where it sends the request to via API to the database. API is the middle mam for every task.
- Scheduler : Scheduler is reponsible for what and when tasks needs to be executed.
- Executor : It only decides how and where the tasks needs to be run, (not like the common execuition of the tasks), Like a middle man between order (scheduler) and the worker (who does the tasks). 
